==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Possibility
<hw>Pos`si*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Possibilities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>possibilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, L. <ets>possibilitas</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being possible; the power of
happening, being, or existing.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧All <xex>possibility</xex>
of error.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Hooker.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Latent <xex>possibilities</xex>
of excellence.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is possible; a contingency; a thing or
event that may not happen; a contingent interest, as in real or personal
estate.</def> <rj><au>South. Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Possible</ent>⟦br⟧
